Joller;-;Gameplay = 10/10 - This is why Arma 3 is my favorite game of all times. The gameplay is unique and realistic. You can actually feel the realism when you play, especially mixed with the awesome community. AI = 4/10 - Sometimes the Ai is completely ed up and this is something the devs need to work on. Graphics = 8/10 - Good graphics, though watch out for FPS drops! Details = 6/10 - No furniture in buildings and other stuff, which makes the game feel empty. But the outdoors (which you mostly play in) has alot of rocks and bushes that can actually save your life in some really hard situations. Though mission makers can add stuff in the Scenario Editor. Replayability = 9/10 - There's alot of things to do, from diving onto land and then sneaking around a guerilla camp to using advanced high-tech mortars togheter with armored vehicles assaulting a largely fortified base. If you combine these things (Combined Arms) you can create some really epic missions. Music = 9/10 - Also I love the soundtrack, it's just pure epicness. Sound = 8/10 - Since the Marksmen platform update got released the sound got a huge upgrade. The gunfire does different echoes/sounds depending on environment and distance and the guns also sound more realistic. Glitchfree = 5/10 - The game has alot of glitches and stuff like that, but sometimes it's just hilarious and doesn't affect gameplay that much. Community = 10/10 - AMAZING COMMUNITY, even the russians stick to their own servers. Though there are some veerry rare occasions of hackers. Also a huge amount of community-mods to use! Developers = 8/10 - At the start of Arma 3 alot of people were saying it was unfinished and they only added expensive DLC (But it looks like they forgo the free platform update!!). Back in Arma 2 the DLC was very worth it and rich of new stuff to play with. Recently, the developers announced their secret project which is a whole new terrain located at an Island in South America! There's alot of new features such as Jetskis and Airplanes which I'm very looking forward to! :D Story = 5/10 - Very basic story, just like Call of Duty. Though there are some mysteries the community must uncover! Length = Long - I think the campaign is about 20 hours long... Optimization = 9/10 - There is alot of optimization, you can even switch colors of the teams. DLC = Medium - There are 3 DLCs at the moment, some people think it's way to expensive (13.99  for 2 Helicopters!?), but they always put ALOT of detail and work into them, and a platform update also gets released. Fair Price = Yes ---------- FINAL RESULT = 97/100
