_DDD;-;This game ruined my life
Omni;-;Arma 3 is an ambitious title with a style of gameplay that will polarize players. The many complexities and amount of controls to master can be a daunting task for any newcomer to the series, while seasoned vets will feel right at home (for better or worse). There is a great deal to learn about playing Arma in a way that is enjoyable. The default campaign mode is passable, with all the tropes you'd expect to find in a military shooter, with a few surprises here and there. Missions vary in length and scope, ranging from short range patrols to full on combined operations assaults. However, where the real meat is in the multiplayer experience and the many mods available. Hopping on to a co-op server with 60+ players who actually want to work together as a unit is nothing short of amazing in a world of "le epic trelling". Being able to request evac, mortar, medical assistance, etc is wonderous on it's own, but having those assets being controlled by actual players gives you a sense of connection and being part of a team. Even if realistic military games aren't your particular style, there are plenty of other game modes available that you can download right from the server browser and enjoy. These include standouts like Altis Life (kind of like a more advanced Cops and Robbers), Wasteland (a survival mod focused on factions), and Breaking Point ( A Day-Z style mod). Mods will breath all sorts of new life into your game, adding new vehicles, uniforms, maps and much much more, giving you almost limitless scenarios and tools to use in creating custom missions. you can check out the large database of mods at : http://www.armaholic.com That said, Arma is not without it's fair number of faults and missteps, the game is not optimized well for multiplayer, and you'll encounter many bugs along the way (most of which are hilarious as opposed to annoying). The learning curve can be fairly steep, and you'll have to be patient to get the most fun out of this title... that said, it's well worth it, especially if you have some friends willing to do the same.
