Krumpetzki;-;There's bugs and glitches everywhere. You will fall through stairs and break your legs, you will crash your car into invisible walls and kill your squad, you will get instantly killed by NPC's from a mile away. You will try to give ammo to your teammate but loose all your items. You will get a monster new PC with the best hardware, but still only get 20 FPS. You will rage and loose all your nerves. But you will love it. Because arma will offer you experiences unlike any other game. You will siege an occupied village in an intense firefight. You will cower behind a tiny rock when your artillery drops bombs too close to your position. You will fight with your fireteam in a deep forest. Your patrol will get ambushed and you will use an old low stone wall for life-saving cover while waiting for reinforcements, hearing bullets crack above your head. And the next day you will fly over that low stone wall in a helicopter and it will be just a tiny speck on the giant arma world, just another memory of a seemingly insignificantly small place. And you will get hooked on it. You will join a team and spend countless nights awake playing with them. You will get mods and tweak. You will learn to code, and you will love every moment of it. Arma... Owning this game is like owning a 2 year old child, its really annoying for a lot of the time but if someone tried to take it away from you youd kill them.
