Cuddles;-;I've had this game since the first day of Alpha, and I can confidentally say that nothing comes close to Arma 3 in potential except maybe Arma 2 and minecraft. It's a fantastic sandbox military simulator where you can do anything you could imagine, no matter how dumb. It's a game where content is developed by the community, for the community. There are no set game modes or official servers, there aren' even any official game modes you can even download on their website. It's a completely player created game. Feel like invading either the islands of Altis and Stratis one minute and then role-playing as a drug dealer the next? Sure, why not. It's completely possible in Arma 3. Pros:  Almost limitless potential.  Close to an unlimited number of gamemodes created by the community.  Hundreds of community made campaigns and mods both avaliable on the workshop and on Armaholic (the go-to place for Arma mods).  Massive maps with none of those dumb loading screens every other game with maps on these scales seem to have. (Stratis is ~15-20km2, Altis is 270km2).  Large maps load very well and are very stable.  The ability to have infantry, armor, naval, and air battles at the exact same time on a much larger scale than you could imagine in another game such as Battlefield.  A wide variety of weapons, vehicles, and clothing. Cons:  Vehicles tend to explode a bit easier than they should.  Possibility of desync occuring on servers if they are overloaded.  Hit markers and boxes can be a bit buggy and glitchy.  Possibility of some pretty big lag. (Adding too many items/vehicles/AI/players to the game's already massive maps). As you can see, the pros easily outweight the cons. This game is fantastic. Even if you don't want to pay the full price for it, it goes on sale often enough and I promise, you won't regret it. 9/10.
