[7-75] Sim;-;I picked this game up when it first came out and have spent tons of time playing it since then. As with all the previous Arma series it has its problems (most of which I believe, should have been fixed before being sold to the public), but even with its faults it is still the closest thing to a real infantry simulator that a non-military person can purchase. With mods the game gets even better and more playable, and less 'sci-fi' like. Also, I've never played any of the single player stuff that comes with the game, I only do multiplayer with my group and I really enjoy it. Things to watch out for; you need a fast processor for this game - DO NOT buy it if your CPU isn't over 3.5 M. All of the Arma games are CPU intensive and this one is the worst for it. Don't expect it to be easy - this isn't Call of Duty or some other 'fps' that has the AI standing around waiting for you. They'll hide, shoot at distance and even chase you around. Use real-world tactics, if you're with friends, and see how well they work (they do), think 'stay alert' and you'll survive longer. There's loads of stuff I could say about this game, but really I play it for about 20 hours or so a week and really enjoy it.
