A.Akis;-;Probably the closest thing that us, the general population, has towards a realistic military simulator/game. I suggest that you do not buy this if you are expecting a linear fast paced action game like CoD or Battlefield, this is much more in-depth then that. This is not simply, running around 360 no scoping people. Squad Managment and effective communication is necessary. There is also something that you can't experience in the said titles above, which is long-range combat. (An example of this is preforming an assault on a base/camp with armor, artillery and other assests from varying distances from your own base. However, this is still a game and should be taken lightly from time to time. I suggest learning how to do tricks in the littlebird (MH9-Hummingbird) and exploiting the terrible physics. This game has multiple different gamemodes and tasks that could be simulated. So you'll never have the same experience twice. Pros: -Very Realistic. -Great Graphics (If you can run them). -Interactive Environment. -Realisitc Vehicals (Most of the time). ------------------------------------------------------------------------ Cons: -Physics (You will hear "Arma Physics" referred to multiple times). -Muliplayer Optimization. -Very steep learning curve but you will appreciate it over time. (More of a learn as you play) -Occasional Crashing. -Controls will more than likely conflict your normal keyboard setup, I suggest using the Arma 2 setup. Overall 10/10 Even if you don't think this is for you, trust me, the teamwork involved in this game is beyond amazing, the amount of co-op I've played counts for 95% of my game time. I've met tons of new people from this and they're like family to me.
