Valkyr;-;I can not in all honesty recommend this game to anyone, and here's why - Its 32-bit - in the most simplest terms this means the game can only use a maximum of 2GB of RAM, there are other restrictions to this but this is the one that hurts performance the most. - Multi-Threading- This should have been a priority during development but instead it almost seems like Bohemia forgot about this, it is poor, and extremely bottlenecked, resulting in low performance. -Realism - A lot of people go on and on about the realism... In vanilla there is only a basic (and I mean basic) "bullet drop" system no realistic ballistics whatsoever without the use of mods, you could literally be in one of the biggest thunderstorms the game could throw at you with gales, rain and all the other lovely things and you will still be able to drop a target at close to a mile away with a precise headshot, simply by pointing up a bit..... There are quite literally dozens of examples of how this game is not realistic, here's just a few. - Vehicle behaviour - is a joke, choppers have been updated in the choppers DLC to be more realistic but even then that means you have 2 completely different flight models for vanilla choppers vs. vanilla jets, obviously they are different one is a chopper the other is a fixed wing jet but here's what I mean, choppers now take into account wind speed, direction, variable gusts, as well as reaction forces, mostly to do with real world physics and all manner of other things whereas the jets simply don't, they feel like they are on rails there is no real skill involded (unless dogfighting) in flying them. Ground vehicles are just as bad there was a more 'realistic' driving model in the original grand theft auto. And that is the nicest thing I could say about it. - Low res vs. high res players - This admittedly is a multiplayer pvp issue so wont affect pve or sp gameplay but ill try to explain it, In pvp (if you play pvp) you will notice your getting sniped even though your behind a bush or shot through a fence or something similar, this is because 'low res' players cant see these details because it is too far away and not yet 'drawn' for them, but they can see you, This is because the draw distance for a character is permanent and un-changeable (it does change but cant be changed by the player, without mods) whereas the detail draw can be changed through changing settings this is in case you wish to improve performance, but this inherently means if you play pvp you have to play with everything turned down just to be on a level playing field. Not very realistic is it? - 3rd vs 1st person in pvp multiplayer, 3rd person players can see around corners, over walls etc, whereas 1st person players cant making 1st person in pvp pointless, nothing more to say. - Player animation - This is the thing that really bugs me to the point I have rage quit in the past, in what possible universe would a person have to stand still in a firefight just to change weapons? There are other animations I detest but that one gets me the most. Note - this can be fixed with mods. - AI behaviour - The AI in this game is a joke, and not a funny one, they are like headless chickens running around with guns shooting at sounds, for example I was playing a game with friends the other night when our pilot was one shotted at over 300m (altitude) from an AI enemy with a bog standard Katiba (which is based on a Khaybar) with its skill setting turned down to 45/100, not only was this ridiculous it is also unrealistic, I have fired assault weapons IRL (not a Khaybar ... Unfortunately) but I can tell you now there is no way in the entirety of the road to hell could you possibly one shot a pilot in a chopper in the sky flying over 300m at over 80mph with any kind of assault weapon, only with a powerful rifle would you even have a chance and even then the shot must be spectacular and ideally head on to the chopper, what have I learned from this... There is no ballistic shielding simulated in vanilla choppers either in its hull (which would be around the cockpit and gunner positions) or in the cockpit glass and if it is, it is in desperate need of an update. I simply refuse to mention AI pilots because they are dead, I killed them all for their incompetence. OK I know by now your sick of me bashing this beloved game, but that's the thing I LOVE this game and like many others I have had hours upon hours of fun playing this, but I cannot get past the fact that this game is so unpolished and so poorly optimised it really does feel like a badly made console port and i genuinely feel the same anger i had with GTA IV way back when the PC version was first released, the random lag or crashing in the middle of the action because the game cant cope with what's going on and just cries in the corner while all the other games just point and laugh at it, the reason i portray it that way is because it feels like Bohemia is dragging its heels and then when it finally has something to give us it overprices it in what is an apparent need for funds which lets be honest makes them look a bit needy - i can understand that though, they need money to pay the staff, but what i don't understand is why they give us so little for our money compared to the like of the arma 2 dlc's in which we got factions, vehicles, soldiers, weapons and missions all in one DLC package i know the price was higher, but for an example Arma 3: Helicopters DLC you pay now 08/05/2015 is 10.99 GBP or $16.95 USD i think.... Anyway what your paying for is the privileged honour of being able to pilot 2 helicopters, that's it, you get everything else for free in an update including the ability to travel in the helicopters, well i suppose that's good right? Wrong basically they tried to tell us this was some kind of great thing they did for us but in actual fact it was so that it didn't split the playerbase, basically covering themselves from flaming on that aspect but i suppose that means most of the people that bought it are going to be decent pilots, not all but most, yes? Well yes actually, most of the pilots i have flown with flying the dlc choppers are good probably about 70% of time, but that means all the really bad pilots vive had in the past all got better at flying? Or does this mean only the people who bought the DLC were the really good pilots with a few people with spare cash thrown in, but if this is the case then Bohemia managed to miss out on a massive cash injection by not putting more choppers into the pack maybe even a custom air force faction for NATO and CSAT its only retexturing some uniforms and some code, its hardly rocket science it takes time sure but still 2 choppers? Its an insult, i just downloaded a mod which gave me 4 choppers and 7 planes with a custom faction, uniforms, soldiers, equipment etc, it took all of 40 seconds to download and hey guess what i didn't spend a penny. Ok this got way too long way too fast so here, conclusion is this i want to recommend this game because i have had a lot of good memories with it and im sure others will like it as well but at the same time i cannot recommend this game for all its flaws, If your willing to put serious time into modding this game then yes buy it, but as i said i cant recommend this because of it flaws and because of the company behind it, i have lost faith in it and cant recommend you buy this. To settle confusion, my pc. - AMD FX 8350 Black Edition 8 Core Socket AM3+, 4.0GHz, 16MB - 4GB XFX Radeon R9 290X DD, 28nm, 5000MHz GDDR5, GPU 1000MHz, 2816 Streams - MSI 970 GAMING, AMD970+SB950, Socket AM3+ - 12 GB Corsair Vengeance RAM - 850W Corsair PSU - 6x 120mm Aerocool Shark 15 Blade
Streaks;-;I really hate to say this, but you should wait to get this game until BIS gets it finished, assuming that happens. The reader should realize that I have almost 2000hrs in ArmA2. The 600 or so listed on my profile here is just since it got added to Steam and doesn't count the time pre-Steam. So, as someone who plays exclusively with friends on listen servers, not on big public servers. As someone who plays mostly CTI maps (remember those BIS?), and as someone who spent most of those almost 2000hrs flying CAS in a jet (remember those BIS?), .......I can honestly say that I'm rather let down by ArmA 3 and it makes me very sad. The interface has always been clunky from way back in OFP and before. The new backpack system seems to me to just be a reskin of the same thing. It does indeed make it a bit easier to use being able to drag and drop stuff (novel!!), and while I appreciate the work here.....I'd rather have seen the time spent on other things. To be fair, two of the devs DID spend time locked up in Greece for a stupid reason. I think it was 11 months? This is something that is strictly forbidden to speak of on their forums for some odd reason. But, I understand this had a huuuuuuge impact on their development cycle as it was their two LEAD devs as I understand it. I get the feeling that they got back, and shoved development through in order to compete with the (then) new BF and CoD releases. I personally feel this was a huge, quivering pile of mistake. Because......they aren't really in competition with those games!!! It'd be like saying that chess competes with checkers and monopoly. All board games sure but vastly different. Same here! ArmA II was all about trying to make the game more of a military simulator. Though I think they had to admit some limitations here and there with the tech of the day without making the engine only playable on super computers. ArmA III seems to go away from this and I think it's trying to compete even more now with those other games in some ways.....maybe I'm wrong? It just doesn't feel like the team is as worried about realisim any longer. For me, the fact that it's set in 2035 is a HHHHUUUUUUUGE turn-off and almost a game breaker right there. That, and there's ONE jet in the game thus far.....one AND it's some old trainer POS to boot.....nice.....well guess this confirms my hunch I've had for a while now. BIS seems to hate fixed wing like Blizzard hates melee! It's all about rotary wing! Which is fine and dandy unless you need an A10 or a Spooky. By 2035 we assume naturally that these have been phased out, so where are their replacements? Hell, at this point I'd be happy with an F15 that I can just fly and do stand-off attacks with from miles away.....oh right that's what the choppers are for! Am I ranting a bit there? Um, yes sorry, but I was just looking SO foward to this game!!! Heck I even did the pre-order on the delux version!! NOW? Ya I'm kinda not happy about that. I fire the game up now and then after I see an update downloading. Just to mess around with the undrivable pickups and do target practice with the assault rifles that have recoil like a .45-110 every shot......it's like going to the playboy mansion only nobody's there. So, I'd say to wait on this game. I'm still playing ArmAII where I can fly fixed wings even in the base game. Oh yes I know...mods mods mods....ya *hangs head*
