JG500;-;Ah, Arma 3. Many people might not enjoy this game as this game unlike most Fast FPS's or Tactical shooters, arma lets you play on a 270km squared terrain. You may approach an objective how you want it, if the mission scenario allows it, when you want it (HVT convoy passing through, gotta be on time.) and with what you want it. Overall the optimization is "okay" as the game recieves constant updates with the biggest one is a FREE Zeus gamemode DLC being released on dev branch. Fixes pour through constantly as well as new features or updates, arma 3 like all the previous arma games provides a simple to use editor which can be used to create a simple firefight, or an all out war with dynamic units and performance scripts. The graphics are really good which helps the immersion, thes a weather setting so you can be having a nice vacation in greece or be infiltrating an enemy base in the stormy seas of Altis, (Altis is the 270km squared island, Stratis is smaller, yet enjoyable) under the cover of fog, as you disembark you grab your gear from the boat, armed with SMG's with flashlights in the night and with the help of moonlight you make your way through the forest, you get to a road. A CSAT convoy passes by, not noticing you. You carry on... This can be the begining of a mission very easily. This is what makes Arma unique, you can script a whole event to make it a michael bay movie or let the players make a critical decision of wether retreating or holding ground. Arma ofcourse features realistic bullet drop, recoil and STANCE ADJUSTMENTS, remember those old fashioned "Stand, crouch, prone" type stances? Well no more! You can now adjust yourself into a variety of stances such as high crouch, low crouch, high stand and many others. You can peek round walls or shove a part of your body out and spray at the enemy. This gives you a whole lot more freedom than many other games, not to mention 90% buildings are enterable, yet without furniture just at the moment. Let's speak a bit about AI, they are currently undergoing changes and they can be very accurate, not accurate, smart or just dumb. As each unit has a skill bar and the games has difficulty levels such as Recruit, Regular or Veteran+Higher which can all be adjusted to multiple points such as HUD, waypoints, friendly skill, enemy skill and much more. They can still provide a very authentic experience. Now, the game is called a finished game, but not all agree. Features pour in and so do fixes. The amount of content compared to previous titles is smaller, but not everything is finished. CSAT+NATO jets are coming in a few weeks as an example. The great thing is that the community is devoted, helping and of all. Active. Mods are rolling out hot from the oven every day, hell. Some people are making a dinosaur mod! And from what I know, official Arma 3 mod tools are not even released. If it's re-skins or dinosaurs, or perhaps Arma 2 content, it is all there and more baking each day. The developers are active and listen to the community and that helps them make a quality game, even better. Yet I do understand alot of people dont like it if they have come from older series such as Arma 2 for "lack of content" or glitches, then they ofcourse dont remember what was Arma 2's launch like :) The game is gradually getting better, and yes I agree arma 2 has "more" content and is more modern combined with the Operation Arrowhead expansion, but Arma 3 is a great game too. Or great modules lacking such as the medic module (A revive like module, for wounded people.) Or great mods such as Advanced Combat Environment or Invasion 1944, most mods are coming over to Arma 3, yet there is a waiting barrier of course. But if you are still confused if you want to buy the game.... Arma 3 cars have working mirrors. I would rate the game at the current state 7.5/10.
