stemajor7;-;Do I recommend this game? Yes I do. If you are coming from console shooters, then the pace might be way too slow for you. But I recommend you stick with it: once you get over the adjustment, you will be rewarded with some really memorable moments. I found my way in to this series with Arma:Gold, which still looks great to this day. They all feature the same basic framework: large open world, your choice of weapon/vehicle/aircraft and a powerful editor for creating your own missions. This is why it appeals to lots of us, because you may have had Airfix soldiers when you were younger, where you set up battles on your bed, using the folded quilt as custom topography. Arma taps into that part of you, giving you the tools to create your own stories. The only limit is your imagination. Other reviewers here Im sure will have commented on the other game modes, so I dont think I need to review them again. Prerequisites to enjoy this game are: 1) Patience, you need to learn the controls, and dont expect to be firing your weapon at enemies every second. You sometimes will have to travel large distance by foot. 2) A PC that exceeds the requirements. It looks fantastic. 3) Toy soldiers as a kid.
