DeathTech;-;Todays review: Arma3 Short Scorebased review: (Longer review below.) Overall [73/90] Singleplayer [7/10] - The game is hard you would do well to save as often as possible. Multiplayer [8/10] - Its great for multiplayer, sadly the in-game browser still lacks refresh button and fails to ever find the server you want to find. On a properly forwarded server still stakes 30m - 1hour of tinkering for your friends to find it. Vehicles [ 7/10] - Vehicles are cool, plentiful, feel well balanced and responsive Weapons [9/10] - Lots of weapons, with now as added bonus you can customize them. Multiplayer Missions [3/10] - Couple of premade missions, most of them proof of concepts no real fun to be had untill you download some from workshop or armaholic. I recommend playing my zeus based map which is like playing with a dungeon master who can spawn everything and anything. If not that use their awesome easy to use editor and make one yourself! Editor [6/10] - It works, but doing advanced stuff requires lots of google usage lots of wiki diving and being best friends with the bohemia interactive website. Also doesn't generate a full mission as it does not include some sort of default description.ext in the mission file. DLC[33/40] 1. Zeus [10/10] - Play as a dungeon master, make a scenario on the go. & Its free. 2. Karting [8/10] - Make races, drive in karts and wear the arma 3 karting outfit, adds racing elements for race lovers. 3. Marksman [9/10] - Adds weapons, loadouts, weaponmods, some items, facepaint, garrage ... Its good, trust me. 4. Helicopter [6/10] - Adds two helicopters, and helicopter pods. Adds sling loading (aka pick stuff up and drop it elsewhere) Long review below: If you have played Arma 2 and loved it you will love arma 3. Its the same game with better graphics, a lot of additions and great changes. Anyone can just say that though so lets get into some specific as to why arma 3 is a great game. For fans of the series and for new players. Lets start with some points for new players. Arma 3 is a realistic military combat simulator. Or that is at least what i'm going to call it. Every iteration seems to contain 2 big landmasses. One is generally a lot bigger. In this case the big landmass you'll probably find yourself always playing on is "Altis". Its big, varied from mountainous to large flats and has a small dessert. The game comes with many vehicles for both ground, air and water transportation as well as combat. We have well known vehicles and newer "imaginary" versions based on existing vehicles. There are also UAV's that CAN be controlled by a single or multiple players. As for the gameplay. You play as the traditional teams Bluefor, Opfor, Independant or Civilian. Movement system is great, feels very fluid and responsive. Vehicles can be damaged as a whole or you can shoot out their tires/engine/... Realistic physics allow for some HOLY **** moments. No Seriously if you have no idea how physics apply to fast moving vehicles this game will teach you by making your car roll over at high speed bends, or lets not forget the time I drove a truck on top of a plane hangar because I hit a quadbike, then bounced up onto a sand barrier, which launched me in the correct angle and with my speed I made it up there. Then I asked an admin for salvation because falling off was certain death! Player damage can range from "just a fleshwound" to holy **** my ****** leg is gone... MEDIC!!!!! If you get shot in a leg you won't be able to run etc... +10 for pain "uhhhh" "ahhhh" "uuuuuuuuhhhh...." Arma 3 is mainly a big sandbox. Missions can let you roam all of it or just a small AO. Still you know at all times that everything you see is somewhere you can go. Almost all buildings can be entered and interestingly with enough explosives, almost all of them can be destroyed into nothing but ruble too. For veteran players: Its arma 2 with better graphics. And some improvements. The old maps can still be played and included with mods. WARNING BUTTON BINDINGS MAKE SENSE NOW G = GRENADE i = INVENTORY Car mirrors now actually work. Lots of overhauls to the core game systems. Helicopters from the DLC pack now can lift, cars, vehicles, boxes,... In-game server browser is still . Arma 3 has a launcher which allows you to play without battleeye if you don't want your computer data compromised. NO SERIOUSLY BEFORE ACCEPTING READ THE TOS FOR USING BATTLEEYE I THINK MOST PEOPLE WOULD DISAGREE IF THEY ACTUALY READ IT, YOU CAN STILL PLAY WITHOUT AGREEING TO IT Arma 3 zeus maps, aka make your own fun on the go, its a sandbox dungeon master, ITS FUN, try it. Arma 3 has arma 3 dayz epoch, its great, try it if you love zombie survival. Racing is now possible. Karting and other vehicles too. AI are improved, no longer  and are deadly at close and long range. Expect to be fighting them like trained professionals because they will wreck you. For the rest its basicly the same as Arma 2. I guess. Simply, if you liked Arma 2 then buy this one... You'll love it... Its worth it. Thank you for your time.
Adzm00;-;Arma 3 takes me back to the days of deltaforce (long time ago), it being a thoroughly enjoyable tactical military shooter, albeit with its own special glitches and graphics fails. The interface may seem somewhat clunky at first but you soon overcome that, and although the game has many controls they quickly become familiar and are relatively intuitive. The scales and graphics on Arma are pretty impressive, although as in many games, the graphics are less impressive up close, less the textures and more the number and complexity of objects, however, with a game of this size if each house was packed with objects, you can bet the frames are going to take a massive hit, what bohemia have done is find a reasonable balance with this. Generally the environment looks great, there are some questionable physics interactions which can make for some strange happenings, although that is part of the charm with Arma. If you want a military sim, that generally plays pretty well with a decent amount of guns and vehicles to mess about in then this is well worth it. Whilst not quite as slick as some games built on newer game engines, Arma does hold up pretty well.
