bd.strelkov;-;If you are considering buying this game, read this first. Let me say this: I really enjoy this game. Its massive open world environment makes it an awesome combat simulator. It comes with fun stock game modes, and has a good fan base. But if you really want to have fun, I highly reccommend playing some mods, such as breaking point, battle royale, and Altis Life, to name a few. PROS: -Large open world terrain -Challenging gameplay -There is a thrill everytime you play. It never gets old. -Good mod support -Lots of vehicles air, land and water -Realistic engine -Almost endless possibilities CONS: -Poorly optimized. Even on my $1500.00 custom build, I still averge only about 40 FPS, dipping to 15 FPS sometimes. this is a minor problem, seeing as my average of 40 FPS is more than playable, however it is still an anoyance. -The game has its fair share of glitches. For example, sometimes I'll be driving behind one of my teammates when his truck snaps back and destroys mine, killing me in the process. Nothing happens on my teammate's screen. Many of the glitches are purley aesthetic, for example, when you die, sometimes your neck stretches out to 5x its size. A bit like BF3. -While the sounds in the game are decent, they are not exactly fantastic. To fix this, get JSRS sound mod. Are you thinking of getting this game just for Altis life? Many people do. Thats fine, infact many of the biggest servers are altis life servers. I play on GSN's Altis Life server. It has an excellent community and friendly admins. Overall, the game is very fun, and a massive improvement over ArmA 2. I would give it 8/10... Thanks for reading. ________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE So, after spending over 200 hours on this game, I will say this. Playing this will change you. If you are a COD player, Battlfield player, etc, you will find yourself 'not challenged' by the gameplay anymore. I've gone back to COD once or twice, and it no longer provides me with the realistic thrill that it once did. If you are in the market for realism, and a game that requires real strategy, get ARMA. Just remember, your play style must adapt. You cannot rush. You cannot spray. (Well, you can, but you will likely die and get yelled at).
