DarkMasta;-;Ahh...Arma 3...love it so much that makes me hate it in the same amount... Arma 3 is not your tipical "guns game" its not an FPS and if you are coming from games like CoD this is NOT the game for you! Arma 3 is a simulation game where you must stop to take a shot, consider the distance between you and the target, set your aim according to the distance of the target, consider the bullet drop if necessary and take the shot! This is a game where you will fall on your belly in the woods and crawl 100 meters if necessary! The game map is something like you have never seen and that sets the right playground to have large (and I do mean LARGE) scale combats where you have soldiers running inside a building to rake refuge from enemy fire, helicopters landing to deploy soldiers, airplanes making a strike at the city and leveling the place, tanks set on a hill 1 kilometer away from the target location along with snipers and all kinds of madness! It is pure epicness and you feel like you are in a war! So if you like those kind of games where you run, jump, do a 360, shoot with a sniper rifle in mid air without scoping, and headshot a guy. This is NOT for you. You must have patience in this game, like I said, you will crawl 100 meters if you need, hide inside a house and die if you are unlucky enough to have a airplane missile dropped on you, peek around a corner and get shot by a sniper, drive an helicopter and it gets shot down! You must be prepared for that but that is why it is so epic. There is no game like Arma 3 that acomplishes what Arma 3 acomplishes. Its the best war game I have ever seen, that I think a lot of people have been waiting for. Games have taken a step foward, and if you played FPS's like CoD and those other FPS's under the radar like Artic Combat or what not and kept imagening "it would be cool to have a game like this but more tactical, with a huge map and lots of players and cool stuff like helicopters, parachuting, having kilometers and kilometers of map to play instead of a close quarter corridor map" This is the game you have been waiting for. But be warned, its so good but it has a huge flaw...it feels like its an Alpha performance wise... It's so frustrating that you can't just, enter the game and play...but you can't because you will play with 5 FPS even if your computer meets the recommended hardware. Its poorly optimized and it sucks to play a game that you should be able to play with max settings and you have to play it with low settings or a find a certain combinations that gives you more FPS's and even then it will LAG and cause things like. You have a guy laying prone in front of you and you press to aim and your FPS's drop just because of that and he kills you, you start shooting and the image freezes for some seconds and the person you were shooting is no longer there...thats the only problem with Arma 3. With that said, its still a thumbs up on my part, but be warned about the problem I just pointed out if you are considering on buying it! To you, do you think the epicness of this game, that no other game can provide, out weights the huge FPS problems? The choice is up to you!
