Gadzy;-;Died and my friend stole all my clothes. Shooting is so hard its like bullets don't come out of your gun. Played epic music as we were dropping out of helicopter... it got shot down. Trolled mates with zeus mode. Providing cover fire for a friend... he got brutally gunned down. Was in the middle of a battle running away from enemies... had to reload. Pinned down got support from a tank... blew us up by accident. 10/10 Best experinces in gaming.
BoomsticK;-;Rating: 4 out of 5 cans of Tactical Bacon. Pros: Open world military simulator. Emulates infantry combat and tactics. Extensive community support means the game doesn't get old through the release of community based mods, scripts, addons and missions. Great mods available (Altis Life, Epoch, Breaking Point, Battle Royale, Exile and more). Realistic and accurate firearms ballistics and ranging (as far as a game can attempt to emulate). Beautiful and well designed maps. Destructible buildings and map features. Huge variety of weapons and load outs especially with the addition of the Marksman DLC (highly recommended). Large number of vehicles to drive. More mature community player base. It's a game where you need to use planning, teamwork and tactics to succeed so it attracts a higher age demographic. ARMA 3 is not Call of Duty, Battlefield, CS:GO. Cons: Prone to bugs and glitching. Death by staircases, insta-exploding helicopters and being sucked into walls is sadly not that uncommon. Deducted a full point for this as it sadly detracts from the quality of the otherwise brilliant game. It is worth noting there is a steep learning curve to the game but this can be offset by utilising the in game virtual arsenal, virtual training and practice scenarios. Will eat your CPU and GPU for breakfast. You need a solid rig to run this with ultra settings. Not a problem for me personally but players do experience FPS issues. Inventory system could do with improvements. DLC content. People however do need to be aware some content requires DLC. Personally I don't have an issue with DLC as it supports the development of the games I like but I do understand DLC annoys some people. Summary: Highly recommended if you would like to experience simulated infantry combat. Not recommended if you want to kill, die and respawn constantly like in a typical FPS shooter. It's a difficult game to master but if anything learn to shoot first. Finding a group to play with that can show you the ropes helps. Learn to communicate meaningful information to your team mates (eg. CONTACT! 2 infantry, bearing 40, 200 metres, left of the house with the orange roof). Effective communication and teamwork is key to succeeding. Check out the mods available and extensive ARMA 3 online guides and wikis.
