Meow;-;Buying this game was probably one of my most amazing and worth while ideas. I would like to thank PsiSyndicate (https://www.youtube.com/user/PsiSyndicate) and Katt (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWogxZyjHckCWxQYnBHmosw) for getting me into the game through their videos and streams. Now, onto the review. Many people complain about the high price tag on Arma 3 (Not including the DLC), but I assure you it is worth every cent of it, however if you cannot afford the game through steam you can pick it up from several diffrent websites for about 1/2 price. I admitt the pricing is a little too steep if you include the DLC however searching around for the right price is as easy as 1 2 3. One other 'let down' for Arma 3, is (If you don't have a gaming rig) that you need a nice computer to even run it at low graphics at over 20fps (Multiplayer). The reason this is such a let down is because with a low-end PC your render distance has to be lower if you want to run the game, this is a huge disadvantage when you are facing people who have bigger PC's because they can see you before you see them. Although there are two up-sides of having low graphics; When I tested Arma 3 in low graphics I found that since the render distance is lower the plants and bushes un-render sooner allowing the player to see people hiding in the bush very easily. The other up-side is that if you run it in low graphics you would have your shadows off, this allows people who are hiding in the shadows be seen as if they were standing in the light. This is probably my biggest issue with Arma 3 because it creates unfair multiplayer gameplay, however it does go both ways with advantages and disadvantages for both high and low graphics settings. The high 'Moddablity' is a huge upside of Arma 3 as it allows for endless fun and new things to try out. At the current moment I am running 142 mods on my Arma 3 with only a few minor bugs here and there, but thats to be expected with that many mods. Another thing is the missions that members can create through the built in editor, you can download many mission files for endless gameplay. These missions can include heli races, races, combat missions, skill building missions, modded missions and many more. The realism in the game ranging from the bullet drop, bullet damage, the AI and aircraft flight. All of these and more if what creates an amazing game. Overall I recommend this game to anyone with the money and a PC that will be able to run the game with at least medium graphics running at 30fps or more.
