Lets be Honest Here;-;A great game that I purchased for around $32 in the alpha early access special. With limited content in the alpha, I expected a much more robust library of content in the future with the beta and release. My expectations were partially met, but the campaign is unfinished more than 5 months after release. Other issues also popped up, as well. While more than capable of presenting its fidelity, the visuals in ARMA 3 tend to tax the system heavily (esp. in multiplayer), and w/ a Sapphire HD Radeon 7870 Ghz overclocked i am getting around 40-50 fps in single player and around 25-35 in multiplayer at very high settings. The control scheme can also be very difficult to learn if you are not accustom to playing an ARMA game, as I was. Overall, I do enjoy the game however. The Altis life multiplayer game type is what I enjoy the most, and breaking point is fun as well. The game is continually improving, but the release date seemed way too rushed.
