Digital_Blauwk;-;Arma 3 Review Arma 3 is one of those games that just can't be put away for very long at all. With endless player-made content, a wonderful modding community, and the most realistic gameplay in a military sim ever, Arma 3 deserves to be Game of The Year , and is a personal favorite of mine. Arma 3 just can not be compared effectively to any other game on the market today. " Military Simulator " is quite a hefty task to do, I'm sure, and Bohemia Interactive nailed it, and are continuing to support the game and update it regularly. One thing for new players that'd I'd suggest is this: The game is meant to played in any way. So expect that with different servers and gamemodes. The most common gamemodes I see today are: "Wasteland"-a team-based survival mode where players must scavange for food, water, and other supplies to live, "Altis Life"-a mode focused on everyday life in Altis, and this does include the criminal part of the island, along with its police counterpart, and finally "Invade and Annex"-this gamemode is all about team work(its a co-op gamemode, so players vs. AI) and tactics to capture all the major areas in Altis. All in all, with its wonderfully crafted enviroments, excellantly made campaign and multiplayer scenerios (most made by other players), beautiful graphic design, and rich gameplay mechanics, Arma 3 is definitely a game that deservest the attention and love its getting. tl;dr Arma 3 is the best, most realistic military sim you'll ever play. 11/10 :D
