Kuzkula;-;Well. Where to start? First off: HARD. This game is almost insultingly hard. The AI let's you know you're boned when the tubes start bellowing out 40mm grenades in your direction. Sometimes they ing cheat, and I tell you, they cheat hard. It's a fun as hell challenge, and I can usually go over 50 kills without getting wiped, but sometimes they barely see you over a hilltop or around a tree and light you up like no tomorrow. This game needs further optimization, however. I can run some pretty insane visuals on other game, and even have gigantic open-world games like Just Cause 2 maxed out, but this one I need to scale down a bit to keep a steady 40-50FPS while still keeping respectable visuals. The weapons are diverse and accurate, but not 'realistic' enough in one simple aspect. You've got all these buttons and lights on a Titan, for instance, to make it fire like a Javelin-style launcher [shoot up, go high, SLAM down], but no way to actually make it do this. This needs to be added. Launching with a top-attack would help with one person, say me, with a laser designator, marking an enemy vehicle on the other side of a hill for an ally with said launcher. The mods are nice, some are even well made! DUWS comes to mind.
