[REF] Malacovics;-;ArmA 3 is a game that focuses on realism without sacrificing all the fun. What you get with the game: -Multiplayer. Many mods (or to be more accurate, missions with scripts) are out there like Wasteland, DayZ (the mod, not the standalone game), CTI (Capture-the-Island, which is like a Conquest mode from Battlefield with a huge map and ArmA gameplay), Domination (which is fairly similar, only it's against AI). -"Competitive" Multiplayer. What this means is that you can experience the "real" ArmA experience. What this means is joining up with clans and operating as a team, as a real army would. This in my opinion is the definitive way to play ArmA3. Clans like this are things like http://www.reacheliteforces.com/ . Look it up if interested. There are many clans out there, just browse the Steamcommunity ArmA3 forums. -Like a dozen showcases which show and demonstrate the new features of ArmA3. -Around a dozen challenges (firing drills) to where you can compete for a better time or train. -3 campaigns, each around ~3-4 hours long (note: only one of them is out so far, second campaign comes on Jan 21st.) -Editor where you can do what the hell you want and can create your own missions or scenarios. -Steam Workshop missions! Download missions made by other players with a click and around two seconds, and play them, rate them. Hundreds of missions are on Steam Workshops, plenty to choose from. BE ADVICED HOWEVER: This game can be a pretty damn big machine hog. You need a pretty decent to PC to play this game appropriately, even more so for the multiplayer.
