Ramloy;-;What can I say? I've been with Bohemia Interactive since 2001 when Operation Flashpoint was born. If you think Day Z or Arma has been laggy, how do you think I felt when I played OFP on a P4 800 Mhz processor with a 1 GB of RAM? Since the release of the latest update, the long awaited "fire your weapons from vehicles" has emerged and Arma 3 has moved one step closer towards it's completion. As for the DLC, first it was karts, then helicopters. The next installment is scheduled for Q1 of 2015 that will feature an enhancement for marksmen. But, that does not go without saying that Arma 3 will ever see a final update, for the game is very community oriented and new improvements are found each and every day. If you are a fan of any sort of realistic gameplay regarding war or vehicle physics, then Arma 3 is for you. Nothing excites me more than loading up a Blackhawk to it's gills and entering a combat zone with my friends and other real players only to delve out utter mayhem and destruction to our enemy. Arma 3 is my favorite game, and if you give it a chance and are patient with it's occasional shortcomings, then get on board and let's annihilate some targets!
