Kerel;-;Slow-paced and heavily strategic/tactical. It's a game that may not be "fun", but it can be very immersive and tries to give you a breathtaking experience. If you're one of those guys that likes hardcore realistic simulation, then this game is definitely the best out there. Also it's more than just a game, it's a platform that has plenty of mods to keep you busy when the original theme of the game is not quite what you're looking for.
Dusk Quill;-;Arma 3 is immersive: as one of the best (if not THE best) military simulators on the market, A3 surrounds you in a variety of breath-taking environments and puts you in the center of the action. You'll receive radio transmissions through bursts of static, hear the wind go by, feel the ground shake when a tank rolls by. Everything from the weather and lighting down to the recoil of the gun in your hand is so finely tuned and detailed, that the only closer you could get to realism is to enlist. Arma 3 is dynamic: it has an arsenal of mods just waiting to alter the game a little more one way or another. With a community thriving on creating more and more for the game, the sky is the limit for what can be done. No two missions will ever be repeated the same way. AI learn and adapt to situations, forcing you to do the same or die, and with a fully destructible environment, nowhere is safe until the enemy are all dead. Arma 3 is intense: you'll know this when you hear the bullets snap past your head and you're holding your dead teammate in your arms. The smallest firefights can shift the course of an entire battle. Life or death can be determined just from which way you decide to lean. Teamwork is tantamount to success, and unlike many modern shooters, there are no "lone wolf heroes", no one guy rushing the enemy line and winning the game for everyone. You work together or you die. There is no third option. Arma 3 is the game you want when nothing but the best will do.
