Ironman71;-;,    .  ,   , ,    -    .       .   .  ,     ,   -  Call of Duty  Battlefield, .
Blackbomber200;-;Hello potential buyer looking through the reviews. Why should you buy Arma III out of all the first person shooters, when COD has basically destroyed the genre. Well let me tell you why you should buy this game. Arma III is a realistic military shooter that simulates every real life thing you would experience in real combat, realistic physics, bullet drop, Weapon Zeroing, fatigue, every little item simulates real life combat. This game is in my opinion one of the best Military FPS shooter out there alongside Halo, Battlefield, and Battlefront. Arma III is first person and third person and features 40 weapons (Assault Rifles, LMGs, SMG's, Sniper Rifles, Marksman rifles, but alas no shotguns yet) last time I checked and over 20 vehicles (Tanks, APC's, Transports) and helicopters. It features several weapon attachments and several body armors and uniforms to choose from. The game is stunningly beautiful you wont find a more beautiful detailed game, the developers put a lot of work and time into graphics and boy did they give you what you pay for. It features 2 large scale maps span across 274 km of terrain (1.6 million placed items)(50 towns and cities). With such high detailed really requires a good computer, I have a ASUS republic of gaming computer with a Geforce GTX 860M and It usually runs Arma at a smooth 60 fps in almost all places including heavy combat and cities, but my computer doesnt work well when it runs high detailed mods/missions from the community. So if you dont have a good computer you probably should wait till you have a good computer. But fps and graphics aside its a very beautifully detailed game when your computer made for these types of games. I have rarely ever ran into any graphics bugs or any poorly textured items, aside the random long necked marine in a helicopter or the pure white eyes of marines. While the game's story faces criticism I think its a well planned thought out story a story you would expect from a war between NATO forces and the local CSAT and AFF forces in the year 2035, the storyline is split into 3 Acts and each is extremely long so youll be sure to get a few days out of it, I wont go more into just so I dont spoil it. The game features showcases and a boot camps so you can learn and play with the basics of the game weather its ground combat, air combat, or showing off new things in the game. Boot camp helps introduce you to the basics of the game. Before I go into the controls let me say about one of the things that greats Arma III great, the Steam Workshop community allows you to download missions and mods that adds some really great stories to continue and add some really great and new weapons or uniforms and some really great maps some like wasteland and remakes like WWII and remakes from Arma II & OA. The community in Arma III is helpful and not once have I ran into some angry little child like I would in COD most people are mature and friendly players who help out and dont yell at you or trash talk. The community is great and friendly and the developers and game makers listen and help the community out unlike some other games. Moving onto the controls and game play, to put it bluntly this is not a friendly game to new players you are going to have to spend hours and hours learning the controls and learning how to play because of the realistic gameplay every single thing you do needs to be carefully planned out and played. The controls are complicated and you will take a long time to learn and play them and when you do play you will use almost every key on the keyboard while playing the game. This game will beat you up if you dont learn the controls or try to run and gun. This is not Call of Duty there is no running and gunning, to survive youve got to move up cautiously, use cover, pick out targets and control your accuracy, which can be controlled with Arma's 19 different stances to improve concealment and accuracy. So if you want a fast paced shooter where its easy to play and just shoot people and they die, Arma is not the game. Arma requires patience you have to work to survive and get those most wanted kills but when you do you will be filled with satisfaction. Tanks and APC's and helis also require skill, communication, and the same caution used in ground combat. And Air travel is no easier, as much as I want to do a cool Strafe run with an attack helicopter I cant cause Ill likely get shot down. The multiplayer really makes this game, Bohemia really put their heart and soul into and boy did they make it great, Arma III has one of the most largest diverse multiplayers of all the FPS's. The servers are great and plenty of ones to choose from, one of the ones Ive been playing the most is Invade and Annex made by someone great who I cant recall (feel free to comment the maker of that great game mode and be sure to check it out yourself) However the AI in this game still need improvement, Enemy AI can either be dumb and take 50 bullets or shoot you dead center in the head and kill you. The Friendly AI are a bit smarter but usually rely on you to hold your hand and kill your enemies. However they are usually very helpful and smart when they want to be, but usually work best under well with a good a squad leader. The enemy AI can be deadly and coordination but are sometimes stupid so you must treat them just like you would any other real player. AI will most likely see improvements in the future and possibly personality traits such as feeling when over run or less likely to stand still and take bullets or savage bodies or take abandoned vehicles. I understand that $59.99 is a lot of money to pay for a game that's been out two years, but trust me I can say without a doubt every dollar and penny is worth it, the developers and game designers spend every penny and dollar improving Arma III and they regularly update the game, However if you are struggling for money just wait for Arma's regular sales, Arma III will fall to $30 and Im sure after long enough it will drop into the lower twenties and even lower. The DLC however is a different story. I got both DLC's with the recent sale and saved some money. While I like the new helis and guns in the marksman and helicopter dlc I believe that they could have already have been in the game. Its overpriced I can agree and youd be best off either not buying it or waiting for sales. Hopefully more ground vehicles and possibly shotguns will be included and hopefully wont be as expensive. On a later note the Zeus DLC is very fun and really adds new gameplay to the game unlike others, to put it bluntly think of Battlefield's Commander but with more power and control, way more.... So as a returning veteran from Arma II and OA I can say without a doubt and confidently that Arma III is one of the Greatest Military Shooters out there, Equally standing up there with Halo, Battlefield, and Star Wars Battlefront. This is Arma III one of the most visually realistic military shooters of all time. You make the stories, you fight the battles, you decide the out come. Will you stand defiant with your team mates and tell your stories, or will you become another causality of the Battlefield. I give Arma III a 9/10 or on another scale a 95/100. Survive, Adapt, and Win. (This review will be updated as time goes on.) For previews or perhaps a better outlook on the game go here -> https://youtu.be/ph1mm2KKSv0
