novaldemar;-;Arma 3 can and will be frustrating to start out with; rest asured it is amazing you just need to do the following: 1. Look up Dslyecxi's guides to Arma 3 - Particularly the movement and shooting guide: https://youtu.be/G8vrbzNYEwM?list=PLQEd6zRLOafWtrQ4EAYKl6z23hvCLYgW6 This will give you an overview of how awesome movement can be in arma when you understand it. 2. Dont start in the campaign. At least dont get frustrated if you find the campaign hard to start with. 3. Instead I suggest going on a Domination server. Particularly if you find one that has infinite sprint. Most if not all will let you test out weapons and play on a team of other players against AI. You will quickly get a good feel of the teamwork in the game and you can ask players ingame if something isnt working for you. Most importantly if you are stuck far away you can respawn at a base and start again without the tediousness of walking simulator that Arma 3 can be. 4. When you get better branch out and try more hard core version of missions. There is hours and hours of fun here to find. You will eventually love walking simulator 2014 :)
