akapanda;-;ArmA 3 is my favorite game of all time. Out of the box ArmA offers an immersive, deep and tense military simulation experience that can't compare to any other videogame. The feeling of being under fire with your life-that's-worth 2-hours is so immersive that I often scream of fear and fun. But to only play the base game is not understanding ArmA. ArmA is a platform for content. There are literally hundres of mods for ArmA 3. Most of those mods are of top-notch quality. Do you want to play on a tropical island? During world war 2? Naval Warfare? Transform ArmA into a flight sim? You name it, it can be done thanks to the amazing game structure bohemia interactive provides. That said, ArmA is not for everyone. But everyone I have recommended it and with whom I've played it (about 5 people now) loves it to death (literally). On top of all ArmA looks the best of almost all pc games. Not because of all the pretty bumpmaps and lighting effects, but because of the scope - one moment you are underwater in a submarine while on the other you may be riding in a tank and firing on detailed bases and enemies while using thermal vision or picture-in-picture. You do need a 1000-dollar rig to even attempt to play this game, but then again: this game is not for everyone. If you've ever wanted to go to war without risking your life or destroying other people's, go buy this game now.
