mrsotko;-;First off, I'd like to say that I have invested over 500 hours into Arma 3. It is easily my top favorite shooter / military simulator ever...aside from goldeneye 64 of course. This game is realistic shooter, where you have to adjust and zero your weapon to the distance your enemy is at. the combat takes place up close, and sometimes over 1-2 thousands meters. lots of weapons, a few different factions, tanks, night vision, thermal, long range combat, bombs, jets, helicopters, all the good stuff. this game isnt a call of duty type game where you are locked in a small map or situation, like a boat. this game is played in the open world, where you can go prone, hide from enemies, snipe them, bomb them, anything! Arma 3 is more of a game engine. There are game types involved that have different gameplay mechanics. some of these types are as follows, but not limited to. Wasteland - Wasteland is just how it sounds. its an open world game where you spawn in with nothing but a pistol and must survive against 60+ other players. find guns, stay alive by finding food and water, make a cache of weapons, team up, and conquer the map. if you die, you respawn, with nothing again. very very fun. King of the Hill - koth is massive battle with 3 total factions trying to seige and capture one city. anywhere between20-40 players on each team fight for a town, the faction that keeps more players alive in the town slowly wins. tanks, helicopters, lots of weapons, and jets can be purchased with money you accrue from killing other players. combat sometimes occurs at 2000 meters between tanks across the landscape. another very fun map there are many more types availible to play, like altis life, breaking point, and day z mod. too many others to name Pros: - game view distance is easily the furthest one can see in any game ever made. but...itll kill your computer lol - lots of cool stuff to use, jets, tanks, helicopters, weapons, and vehicles, - moddable lots of cool stuff to do - realistic. bullets drop over distance, zeroing of weapons, realistic combat distances, - big! the maps are large and big enough to accomadate lots of people Cons: - bugs. the game consists of various non game breaking bugs and such that never seem to get fixed - unoptimized. the game is unoptimized period. i run it at ultra with dual 980's and get 15-35 fps in multiplayer games. changing the graphics to a lower setting helps little, it just runs slow...there is no question to it My youtube channel shows the game and a few of its mods. check out my video on the wasteland mod https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJOE9xZRiIg
