Goose;-;ArmA III is quite different from most other first person shooters. As to be expected since it is a military simulator. With it's clunky UI, desync problems, unexplained gameplay, complicated controls, and many other bugs, it is clearly not perfect. However, when you get past the UI, and have played the game long enough to understand how it works, ArmA III offers some of the best experiences in video gaming. There's nothing quite like a 100 vs 100 match that turns the colossal Altis map or the still giant Stratis map into a war torn battlefield. The true heart to this game is the mods, and boy are there a lot of them! To start, I would suggest checking out Altis Life, Battle Royale, and Wasteland. These mods add so much life to the game. Many of these mods feel like complete individual games themselves. In short, though there may be some bugs and a steep learning curve, there is no doubt that ArmA III offers arguably the best multiplayer experience in video gaming. - 9/10 would glitch again
