Ophyzarr;-;A vast improvement on the previous titles. ArmA 3 delivers on so many levels. Many mechanics have been wholly reworked and large steps have been taken to make the game more intuitive and accessible to players new and old. One of the most striking leaps in development is the new stance and infantry movement system which along with the new ArmA 3 control scheme makes it a whole lot easier to control the player. As with any addition to a game series, the graphics are usually updated and the visuals are absolutely stunning with ArmA 3. The environments look lifelike and have meticulous detail put into them, the detail rivals games which have no-where near as vast of a game world as Altis or Stratis. There are drawbacks with the game such as a lack of content (weapons, vehicles and aircraft get boring quickly), but with previous titles in the series (ArmA 2 most notably) there was a huge drive in DLC and mods providing potentially endless amounts of fun in the included sandbox and level editor. Optimisation has also drastically improved, I receive much higher frames on higher settings than in the previous title, which is a real game-changer. All of these improvements have made it so much more fun to play the game. There is nothing comparable to playing this game with a large organised team. It's my personal recommendation that if you were ever interested in the ArmA series, now is the time to purchase and that it is 39.99 well spent.
