Neo;-;I think that a lot of people are afraid of this game because they see the ultra-realistic warfare videos made in this game on YouTube but you really shouldn't be. This game isn't just for those realism enthusiasts, this game is also for those who like sandbox games. You can create your own scenarios to play with friends or alone. The editor is very great in this game right off the bat, but if you take some time to learn the more advanced options of it you'll be able to create some really neat scenarios. You can create a hostage rescue mission, a go-kart race course, and many more. This is really fun to play around with by yourself if you don't have friends that are into this game. The game is very well optimized, taking a huge step from Arma 2. There's a lot of free content being put into the game such as new guns, vehicles and many bug fixes every month. The game is constantly being updated to provide the best experience. Online gives you a huge variety of scenarios, from zombie survival to Battlefield-style conquest, even to regular deathmatch in small to large areas. There are lots of guns in this game that can all be customized with various scopes, magazines, flashlights and more. The gameplay/controls take a while to get used to because they are so weird at first but eventually everything will make sense and feel very natural, though you will have to re-learn it if you take a long break from playing the game like I did when I stopped playing for a month or so. Overall the game is very great, especailly with friends on your own scenarios. I'd reccommend this game mainly to lovers of sandbox games for how easily moddable it is and how easy it is to create scenarios. 9/10 my favorite in the Arma series
