RedShadow;-;Tested the game during the free week-end on 2014.26.10 I have played Arma 2 and I am a fanatic of realistic military/tactical simulations, like the first Ghost Recons, Rainbox Six, America's Army, Insurgency, etc. Note that right now I am at the Tipping Point mission, and I only played single player. BTW I cannot finish the mission since I cannot for the life of me get into the speeboat. I can drown under it though. I also completed the entire tutorial which was very well made. +1 for this. However the first impression of this game ain't good: The "simulation" part is very lacking . Simulation? Nah... for real? The first missions goes way too fast , to the point that my dude is always totally tired following the team leader. Everyone moves around, and in the end they get shot. You end up the only one remaing and have lone wolf your way to the rest of the mission. I was expecting a very slow pacing, like Ghost Recon. Nope, team runs ahead and they don't wait for you. Since I try to loot bodies to build up a nice gear and be confortable, I stay behind while my team rushes away. I even didn't do jack in a mission since they were rushing so fast that they completed the objectives all by themselves! I was litterally crawling my way and looting sht while they were sprinting ahead. Mission completed by the AI only lol. Wow. Weapon handling is basic and very accurate. I meant too much accurate. I haven't noticed any bullet drop when shooting over 200 meters for instance. No compensation was required, just aim and shoot. Tangos accuracy however is insane. They drop to prone and headshot you. I couldn't test a sniper wwapon though. But no jams, fast realoding wether your mag is in a pouch or or backpack, it magically appears in your hand and goes straight to the mag well. The gear now, is mission specific. I litterally spent hours on customizing my gear to prepare for the next mission. Looting dead bodies and stuff. Optimizing weight. Now the end of the day approaches and night comes. So I'm like hopefully I grabbed some NVGs and I have an IR laser. Yeah. Next mission starts, my gear has been stripped. Backpack has disapeared, vest too and I end up with a short barel weapon, a FCKING FLASHLIGHT and my  to fight. While, of course everyone else is tanked with 30lbs of nades, NVGs and stuff like that. I regroup and I am given an NVG and a laser. Great. But why... now? In the middle of nowhere when we were 1 click away from base? WTF. I even tried, because I was so pssed that at every mission I start basically naked, I tried to go back to base on foot. Yeah climb that hill up and base is there. But nope. Radio says: turn the fck around soldier, you are walking towards a minefield... ahah so I'm like avoid the thousand claymores scattered around, when I suddently die. I was not moving. In other word: linear. And I'm not done raging on the gear yet : yes soldiers ain't supposed to have custom gear. I am fine with that. What I am not fine with, is being the ONLY ONE in the team that has dck. Which is totally incomprehensible since HQ has gear and stuff. So why? At the missiong overview, when we see the map, we can customize the gear there. BUT no support item is available! Which mean that my lovely prepared backpack IS GONE with everything inside of it. Gone forever man. Waste of time: clearly a game for non-thinking players; hop in mission, play, don't loot because no time, and don't question your gear you sht soldier. And also, you can't have a custom gear, but you can loot the opfor AND take their weapons? Ever heard of NEVER picking up a tango weapon because it could be IED RIGGED uh? Simulation hmm... nope. As for the scenario it's pretty bad IMHO. Mean soldiers attacking civies, and then NATO. The latter having to defend itself. So 4 NATO guys against 30 tangos is fine, no big deal. Missions are scripted and loosing a team member will not trigger a mission failure. Hopefully. Nothing much though, a lot of walking around. Not much tactics there, but at least some strats could be cool. Sometimes there is flanking. But not much. Want to use smokes? What are those for? We rush dead on, on tangos... The IA can see tangos behind hills. Yeah. My OWN DUDE can see an UNKNOWN CONTACT on the EAST 1.5 clicks away! Damn man you good! http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=332462626 I end up shooting at the HUD squares that my buddies report. I can't even SEE the enemies that are super far away behind bushes, tree branches and stuff. How the hell can they spot them, while running like crazy >.> Simulation you said? Getting hit doesn't make you fall on your ss. It does in AA if I remember correctly. However your "accuracy" will be screwed. Or not really: your movements becomes eratic. Like your iron sights move around by themselves. But it is still Unreal Tournament accurate provided you shoot at the right timing when the crosshair is right on the tango. I like better the Arma 2 overall weapon experience, with the weird deforming crossair: like Rainbow Six. That way, you cannot see where your shots will land. In the end, having played a lot of America's Army 2 and a bit less of AA3, ArmA 3 is good, yeah, but definitely LESS realistic that those both. Insurgency stays the best simulation so far, but it's not an army sandbox sim: it is way more focused on CQB. Finally the default game setting are much too easy. Tougher armor, can seeing in real time your buddies moving on the map, you can see how many bullets are left, etc. Not a simulation: try the Elite settings instead, and remove the crosshair in addition. Now we are talking. Other stuff Graphics : I say awesome. Configuring this is easy and seamless. FPS are computed while tweaking options which is super great. +1 for this. But no FOV configuration so that's -1. Game tweaking : awesome again. Colorblind people, be not afraid. Well not that much anyway. You can change the ingame HUD colors. Which means that way points, tangos spots and stuff can be customized. Yeah the base color were blending, for me, with the surroundings. So I changed the colors to very bright yellow. Now I can see. Remember though that everyone has BDU and it's all green, brown. Hence I have a extremely hard time to spot enemies unless they move. I had the same "issue" with AA. In the end I recognize them thanks to their different weapons and of course their location. But some missions are SNAFU when the friendlies are surrounding a city. :/ cannot distinguish who is who. But It's alright, that's just me. Sound : Great nothing to report here. There is ingame music (sometimes) which gives... a bad vibe. Like we are in a movie/CoD game sht. I just don't like that, that is all. Up to 128 sonds sources at the same time. I like that. And you can disable music :) Spacialization works very well with my 5.1 speakers. Can hear stuff behind without problem. Conslusions I recommend the game, still. I can feel the amazing amount of details in the game. It is polished, and this is great. The huge flaw here is the "simulation" part that fails hard. I am playing almost a CoD clone, not an improved Arma 2. Sorry. For this reason, the free pass didn't convinced me. At all. I enjoyed playing but I really wasn't afraid of dying nor was I afraid of bad tactics: ain't nobody got time fo dat. Too fast is my final conclusion. I creep in the dirt, I don't run like a crazy monkey on a road you know. I will buy the game, but much later, when the price will have dropped even more: right now is around 22 and it's on -50% sale. Still too much. For me, for what I was expecting. If you are looking for a better realistic army infantry simulation, then America's Army 2 is still the best out there. AA3 is good too, but is more "frenetic", like ArmA3 is compared to ArmA2
