Dance Commander Aerdoria;-;One of the better games (if not THE best) on my list in which you have complete and absolute freedom. The editor itself is a very fun feature and you can do practically whatever, as long as you dedicate some time to learning how to script or the syntax, or whatever. In any case, an amazing game which I truly enjoy playing with others co-operatively, but also PvP. The combat is fun, somewhat simple, but surely adrenaline-pumping and full of action. If you're playing with the right people, it's a relaxing, beautiful experience which helps team-building, teamwork, leadership and orientation quite a bit. The new features (stances) are amazing. Holding control and pressing w,a,s or d acts responsively and puts you into a certain stance. The controls are easy to learn, flying isn't all that difficult if you have some patience and the nimble-ness to use auto-hover. Armoured vehicles (for now) contain only Armoured Personnel Carriers, but there'll be Main Battle Tanks soon, which is AMAZING. The names are altered, but you might recognize how the Zamak trucks are actually Kamaz trucks! (THE MORE YOU KNOW!) Anyhow, the aircraft (helicopters for now!) are amazing and perform quite well. My favourite? I don't have one for now! But onto the weapons, which I find sauce. Weapons are highly customizeable and allow for dynamic attachments and replacing the aforementioned. Stealth operation? Slam a suppressor on. Long-range? No problem, here's a scope. And it all goes together very well, but the content is still lacking. However, it's a beta and I can't wait for the actual release of the game (which will be amazing, as the beta is saucetastic as it is). To anyone who wants to explore a mediterranean-esque island, I truly suggest purchasing this game and going crazy. As I said, you have a lot of options, the editor itself, you can craft campaigns in that thing. As stupid as it seems, it can be something better than singleplayer/multiplayer combined. It's all down to you and how you wish to play it out. You could even try roleplay servers and be a civilian. But that's not what this is about. This is warfare. 10/10
