james;-;Excellent 1st or 3rd person tactical shooter. More cerebral than most. If you're tired of twitch FPSs and totally stupid AI who forget you exist when you go behind a tree then this might be right up your street. An easy to follow tutorial gets you ready for the single player campaign. I've only played for a few hours so far but I'm hooked. And it is BEAUTIFUL! The island setting is so rich that I get a great sense of immersion and tension. Combat is sudden and brutal. Loving it. 10/10
PFC Valls [29th Ret.];-;Been here since first Arma, I've seen huge improvements, and still a long way to go. Arma 3 is way better than Arma 2. The alpha version itself has fewer bugs than the released version of Arma 2 - but that doesn't mean it is bug free. I play it in a realism unit and we use the game extensively, trying to get 100% of what the game can offer, either using Zeus or other mods to improve the experience. The scenario depicts an unstable region, currently constituted by two Greek islands located to the south of the balkanic peninsula, on the Aegean Sea. The first one is Stratis (Agios Efstratios - https://www.google.com/maps/@39.5122819,25.0139011,13z) and the second one is Altis (Lemnos - https://www.google.com/maps/@39.9023965,25.226326,26328m). Bohemian crew actually went to those islands and took pictures of the towns located there, so the in-game cities looks almost exactly the same as the real cities (Just like Kavala, in Altis, that looks very much the town of Limnos: http://youtu.be/e5urNdAogpA). There are four factions struggling for power in this region. They are: NATO (North Atlantic Treaty Organization), CSAT (Canton Protocol Strategic Alliance Treaty), AAF (Altis Armed Forces) and FIA (Freedom and Independence Army). In all missions, the game depicts CSAT as an invading force, and NATO as the peacekeeping force. AAF and FIA are local forces, and their allignment varies along the missions. The game still has some latency issues, lagspikes, dedicated server crashes frequently, the framerate is extremely low (tops 25) even using the "standard" settings over a high-end rig, the learning curve is very steep if you didn't play the previous titles from the franchise, but once you get things going, it is some unique FPS experience that no other game can give you (and I've played enough of them to know about that). Be aware, if you're willing to hop in a server, grab your gear, walk 10 steps and start killing people, this game is not for you. This is a complete combat simulation suite, focused on realism, which means that usually if you spawn too close to action, you'll die and you'll never know where from. If you fly your helicopter too close to the objective, you'll probably be shot down. If you drive your Hunter directly inside a hostile city, you'll probably gonna blow from land mines or AT soldiers. Be ready to drive cars or pilot aircraft for 10 minutes, then park the vehicles and walk for 5 more minutes prior to hope for any action at all. It is a great game, and if you are a fan of simulation AND combat genres, this is the perfect mix of both. For some footage, check out my youtube channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/PFCValls
