Mana Break;-;Crazy Developer:"What about making an open world based simulation shooter with good graphics, many weapons and really interesting vehicles? But since it has to be something special, so lets set in the the future and maybe add something like... like DIVING and flying JETs, and using UAVs and using Artillery tanks and much more. But since 300h playtime is not enough for us, lets add FULL MOD COMPATIBILITY AND a built in editor." Programmers:"YES LETS DO THIS!" And well. This is Arma 3. A mod compatible first person shooter set in the future with an open world and MANY ways to solve a (multiplayer) mission: Diving? No Problem. Sniping? No Problem. Driving in full-ham using tanks? No Problem. In other words. Arma 3 is a sandbox. A shooter-sandbox. You like zombie games? Just download and play the breaking point mod. You like RPG (with soldiers, civilians and even Suicide bombers? Then join an RPG server. You like the vanilla gameplay of tactical shooters? Join a vanilla server. You'ld like some modded gameplay with lets say 20, 30, well no >50 modded weapons? THEN GO AHEAD, DOWNLOAD MODS AND JOIN A SERVER USING THE SAME MODS! But there is one thing which may turn down some "xXxCoD-Fanboyz". The realism. You got shot in the lag? OH, YOU WONT BE ABLE TO RUN THAT LONG ANYMORE. But realism doesnt mean that the game is impossibly hard. It just means that you have to play as a Team while using tactics. The main problem of the whole game is the optimization. While PvP-only servers work pretty well on my "normal" PC with about 30-40 frames, servers having many AI's will make every PC die. The frames will drop to 10-20, even if you dont see the many AI Soldiers running around. Still go ahead and buy this game. Every Teamplayer who got bored from Battlefield of Duty: Medal of modern warfare and 08/15  will enjoy this game :)
