Not Deidara;-;Iz epic EDIT: Ok so since people probably didn't find this review good enough, I decided to write a real, professionally made review. Pros: First off; the controls are way better, more customizable and generally feel nicer. Secondly; the graphics are absolutely beautiful, and I even got this to (sorta) run on my laptop. Which is wonderful. And finally; The multiplayer is a lot more open, as far as ive seen. You've got Zeus, which is fun when you play with friends, theres Altis Life, Wasteland, and a lot of things I haven't seen in Arma 2 yet. Oh, and Steam Workshop support. Incredible. Cons: As i said earlier, the graphics are absolutely beautiful. Which means you need some high-powered NASA computer to run this on the highest graphical settings. Or you can switch to lowest and have no lag at all. Which in return gives you the world's worst eyecandy. Theres also the long download times (from my experience) when you enter a server with the slightest hint of addons. It seriously took me half an hour when I tried to join a regular Co-op server. Neutral thingys: This game requires a lot of patience and tactical knowledge. And with a lot, I mean like a crapload of it. This isn't your stereotypical pew pew FPS. This is (As it says in the game desc) a military simulator . You'll rarely encounter baddies (from my experience), and when you do its bang bang and you're dead. Which is useful when you're on the winning side. I mean, theres just no hitmarkers. Only death. (I'm looking at you, CoD.. grumble grumble)
