Maine Coon;-;There are lots of bugs and poor design choices, that's for sure. The graphics aren't that great and the game runs like crap (sometimes 25 fps on my top end system). The game can also be really boring and frustrating (like when you get stuck on rocks and have to restart a 2 hour mission). That said, I definitely recommend this game for someone who's tired of the same ol arcade shooters. Before I played Arma, I thought Battlefield 3 was a military simulator (lel). This game is nothing like call of duty. In arcade shooters like CoD, there's tons of action, all the time, and it gets mind numbing. In Arma, action is pretty infrequent, but when it does happen it's really intense and unforgiving. The missions are also very sandbox; you can plan out your own strategies instead of just running through ACTIONPACKED!!!!!, repetitive levels. It's a hard game to learn. It uses almost every button on the keyboard. To this day I still don't know how to do some things, such as use laser guided bombs. If you're looking for a challenging, intense "true pc game" you can't go wrong with Arma III.
