Zag;-;Missing Alot. Enough sed.
Crowley;-;This is more of an "infantry simulator" than a computer game. It's an FPS but with Flight Sim controls and realism. The tutorials are called "showcases", which is not at all helpful or descriptive. If you're coming to this for the first time you'll likely make the same mistake I did and try to do the campaign first. The sim itself is insanely hard. The realism means you'll often come under almost instantly lethal fire from shooters who are completely invisible to you, and that's just in the tutorials. Even when you can see the enemy, they're often dots on the horizon who can nevertheless pick you off behind cover with unerring accuracy. Ammo is incredibly restricted, meaning I was actually glad when one of my team got killed because it meant I could resupply. There may be a way to get resupplied without your teamates dying, but like so much of this game, it is not obvious how to accomplish that. The controls are far from intuitive. It took me the better part of an hour and some editing of the control menu to get the gun optics to actually come up reliably when I clicked the right mouse button. Much of what you are supposed to do happens through the "order menu." I think you're meant to use this (maybe? again, it isn't clear) to order NPC team members to do stuff, like attack a particular target, but it is far too unweildy to use in combat. To select the "order menu" you have to press '0' or '~'. '~' didn't work and the font chosen means it isn't obvious if you should be typing 'o' 'O' or '0'. It's zero, btw, but zero on the number keys at the top of the keyboard. Zero on the keypad does something else. The keys can also do different things when modified by alt and ctrl. In the middle of a firefight. Where you die instantly to targets you can't see. Navigation seems straight forward until you try and apply it and realise that waypoints don't actually appear in your HUD, or maybe they do and I just don't know which button/menu item to select to make them visible. Even the inventory system is overly complex. If you try and loot a corpse you have to loot each individual part of their kit separately (clothing, webbing and pack). Not realising this for the first hour and a half contributed substantially to my shortage of ammo. I've tried the campaign and the first 2 showcases. I can't complete the 2nd showcase, because on the rare occasions I don't get insta-killed by the hostiles, the anti-aircraft missile is unguided and I don't have the knack for hitting moving targets with it. I've died at least 100 times so far, >20 of those to land mines, which are also invisible. A punishing exercise in misery and frustration. Not recommended.
