eNvy;-;I did enjoy the gameplay and story of the game, and i'd definetly play another sequel. It was worth the purchase.
BibleClinger;-;Arma 3 is a cross between a game and a military simulator. It is more complex than the usual big-name games like Call of Duty and Battlefield, making the learning curve potentially intimidating for beginners. In reality, however, if you can handle typical FPS games, you can figure out the basics of Arma 3 in about a week. The reward of sticking with it is immersion in massive, beautiful, outdoor environments (the smaller island of the two is about 20 km while the larger one is 270 km), tactical play, and epic encounters. There is something different about scrambling for cover as you're being shot at by an enemy patrol, and not knowing where it's coming from -- and then after you find out, having to use compass readings to share that knowledge with your teammates. It's also incredibly fun to take an AI squad under your command close to an enemy position, assigning targets to them individually, and then ordering them all to open fire at the same time on the unsuspecting soldiers. Notwithstanding all of this, quite possibly the best part of Arma 3 is its open nature. While you'll probably enjoy playing the stock Escape missions, you'll soon discover that there is a treasure trove of custom scenarios created by the community. This is one game that is worth the price just for the community creations alone.
ExoTic_LeGenD87;-;This is my favorite game ever it is really fun i rate it a 10/10
AHyperionSpy;-;It's overall not a bad game but for the price I wouldn't recommend it. Pros: * Beautifully detailed world spaces teeming with wildlife * Extremely large maps make for fun and challenging combat as well as virtual site seeing * A nice assortment of weapons and equipment to choose from Cons: * Poor help system and no tutorial for new players - One was later added but it was not super useful * Overly complicated and over numbered controls with a large portion of the keyboard being used as well as the mouse * Poor sound effects; especially for guns * For as detailed as the world and NPCs are, the guns seem to overall be lacking in both function and appearance * Although certainly more realistic than most FPS games, the fatigue system is a little troublesome considering how large the world is and how far you often need to travel from objective to objective without a vehicle. Even walking with an average amount of gear can almost completely stop your progress fairly fast forcing you to stop and rest Overall score from 0 to 10, 10 being the best: 5-6
