Taco land;-;I was having a fun time on this game. It's a next generation Military game for sure. With it's Amazing Graphics, Heart racing battles and realisim, I am going to say 10/10. But, For fans of Arma who have been playing for a long time like me, They will notice major changes that will make them feel like noobs all over again. And it just does not have that feel arma always had. Nore does it really have the same setting. But still it is a great game. Also, If you intend to play offline or with a buddy against the AI, I seriously recommend getting the FFIS (Fire-Fight Improvement system) Mod. It will make the AI much smarter but also more realistic and make there precision with guns less accurate. Originally the AI will Lay down or crouch and sit in the same position for the whole battle while firing with in-realistic accuracy and sometimes even instantly snap there aim to you regardless of where you are. The Campaign has improved majorly since the last time I reviewed Arma 3; Enemys seem to be placed better and move toward you better, Some items that make the game easier or harder have also been removed, Some AI are as stupid as hell though. Also, If you find the current factions to be a bit bland or lacking a lot of content then take a look at the RHS: Escalation Mod. It add some new factions with countless vehicals and weapons and customization options to the game. I also recommend downloading addons from the steam workshop. These include: Gamemodes, Missions, Some weapons, New Units and much more to improve Arma 3 or repair something wrong. That is what I have to say for now. To divide the review up in numbers. Content on purchase: 7/10 Dlc content: 5/10 Free down loadable content (Mods): 8/10 Community: 6/10 True to genre: 9/10 Overhall: 10/10.
