TurtleGamer;-;My 1st real experience with ARMA 3: SO, I join this random server, everyone at base, grandpa commander was yapping on to everyone telling us all to get to our squads and so on, didn't really pay much attention, some random bodies on the floor, t-bagged em' while looking at fellow team mate. Suddenly see a group of guys in scuba outfits, thought they looked call, the goto grandpa commander asking for heli, he calls one over, they say I need to join their squad to go with them (whatever that meant) 3 more guys followed me and the scuba guys into the heli not knowing what we were getting into. Inside the heli I joined their squad, after a white we get dropped off on a cliff near the ocean, and team leader says to follow him. we walk like 1k till we see the radio tower, our objective, looked like no one was there, looked easy. Team leader assigned us all a buddy so we'd work as small teams. We move on closer to it, come upon a small hut 300m out of the radio tower and team leader says he's going down with a couple of us while the rest of us stay up to support him. He moves down and they plant the C4 on the tower, team leader says "its gonna blow stay clear" and it slowly falls down. We suddenly start to spot enemies moving on the hill over the tower, veichales, with big guns, small infantry teams, moving quickly apon them. So they get behind a small area covered by bamboo, me and the others including a sniper start taking out enemies on the hill. Teamleader called us all to move in except the sniper, we quickly move in and join upto them. We hold off behind the bamboo for a while and a veichale starts moving in, we all panic and fall back a bit, but he eventually goes away. Teamleader orders us to move up into the small house there was near the tower so we do, we get a small resistance force as we moved in, didn't take long to take them all out, we hold position for a while and teamleader says we were suddenly the only attack force in the AO. Everyone else was at base listening to grandpa commander. We fight off a few more small forces until it began to get dark, all of a sudden it went quiet, all we could hear were crickets. Then out of no where contact from the west, contact on the north we were scattered out around the house, some of us including me take hits, medic came and quickly patched us up so we could continue to fight. Fighting became impossible, some were low on ammo, without night vision you couldn't see a thing and most of us didnt come with nightvision scopes on our guns. Quickly a bigger force moved onto us, veichales battered at us from all sides, grandpa comander says the main assault force had moved in, all souteast of our location, our medic ran out of medkits, we struggled to keep off the enemy and then our sniper left, cut down to a 6 man team we struggled to keep the enemy away. The main force had battled to the center of the AO, when then our team leader gets hit, medic can't revive him. We struggled to fight off the enemy, no more infantry were around but an enemy veichale had us cornered near the house, I realise my buddy wasn't here and we called for him, no answer I told my superior i was going to check on him, as i move up to his position i realise he was out, shot by an enemy, I call it and carry his body back. We try reviving them but no luck, so my superior says we were going to move up to catch up with the other squad, as we began they say the AO was captured and mission was ended, the superior said for us to move up to heli and leave the bodies behind. We sprit toward the propellars we hear of a near by heli, as we approach it, it suddenly begins to take off, the superior shouts "WAIT FOR US WAIT FOR US!" it waited as we all got on, another squad was already on it, we waited for another one of ours to cath up, and he then says the heli was full, and couldn't come back for us, as we all looked at him, he took his own life. The heli began to take off, we didn't say a word the journey back. That, Is ARMA 3.
