Stonewall Jackson;-;Sgt Jackson 31.05.15 Final Entry Stranded, we have been caught in a bitter fire fight lasting over 2 days. Ambushed, as we attempted to flee from the island by an elite infantry unit, we sort refuge in an old farm house. My men and I fought bravely, holding back the enemy. Contact to HQ has proved fruitless, they have abandoned the island and the few soldiers that remain. My thoughts in this quiet period turn to family and friends back home, my lovely wife and two twin boys. If they somehow get this journal, I want them to know I love them dearly... I cannot dwell too long, I can hear the enemy. I hold back the tears to keep face in front of my men. We have seen that the enemy do not take prisoners of war, in fact they make an example of captured soldiers in a truly horrific manner. When captured, you are stripped of your items, and forced into a vehicle drove by the AI, the driver is given a way point from one end of Altis to the other. you are not allowed to leave the vehicle or drive the vehicle yourself. They are barbarians. My men and I are down to our last rounds of ammunition, I myself only have my side arm. We know we will not survive the next assault. I have thought about saving one round for myself. but I don't want those s out there to have that kind of satisfaction. My engineer Kevin, a brave man with a mustache worthy of a medal on its own merit, he approached me and told me he has one explosive charge left... We discuss our options. Knowing full well our situation, Kevin, Johnson, Taylor and I have decided the last man standing will detonate the charge, we will go down fighting to the last. The charge is set. I'm not a religious man but if there is a God, may he have mercy on our souls. I hear the enemies battle cry. Farewell Despite the occasional clumsy AI, This game is that realistic. Just fantastic, BUY IT NOW.
