Trices Mailwind;-;I used to like Arma quite a bit, number two and three. I was one of those players that would hop servers looking for a good time, try and do something sort of coherent, get my  annoyed in by a certain portion of the player base that should not be mentioned, *Cough* Ginsberg *Cough*. I had my fun with the game, and that was about it. But then I hit the REAL MEAT of the game, community. Being able to play with a group of buddies is the peak of enjoyment from atleast vanilla Arma. You toss Arma's beautiful modding community into the mix, and this becomes a very different ballgame on the same field. When I happened upon a small, friendly community that I would soon dub, "a bunch of jolly s," I fell in love with Arma on a completely new and fantastic level. About 600-650 of my hours logged where in the span of a year playing with these guys, and it was a fantastic time. The more you have available to you, like a personal server, the mod base, ability to use the editor, the more depth the game has. That all compound on the imagination of you and your buddies. Wanna screw around? Go ahead and run across Altis with your  hanging out, thumb up your , barfing rainbows on those who stand in your way. I'm not saying your can do this, Because you may be able to put that together IF your determined enough, or IF someone else is. Want to do something Para-seriously, with proper radios that can be really crappy because who the hell put that mountain there, call signs etc., go ahead! This game can be a pretty cool thing to hop on and kill  on, and it could also be a real ing hoot of a time wrecking  with your own band of Jolly s. If you can handle the realistic Mechanics and enjoy this style of FPS, I say this game is a MUST HAVE. If you struggle with the games that aspire to be highly realistic, this probably wont be for you. Some other very useful traits of character to have going into this game is the maturity to play cooperatively with atleast a neutral disposition when playing with others, and patience to sit through some long chopper or car rides which can hand in hand with maturity and being able to contain yourself.
