HooksGURU;-;A tactical sim, that only has aspects of a game. ARMA III is not intended to be a "game." It does not have the action most are used to from today's millitary shooter genre. What it does have, it has in spades. A deep simulation environment that spans accross some of the largest landscape to be placed in a title thus far. A plethora of weapons and set ups allow for equipping the perfect blend of survival and attack. The ability for user made content to be easily added to the base of the files, adds for creativity and fun. ARMA III is a title that asks you to make your own fun. It will not be for everyone, and even those who may enjoy camping out with a sniper rifle for hours on end, may find it dry and cumbersome. However, if you are looking for one of the more realistic takes on millitary shooters. ARMA III will have what you are looking for. Even if it doesn't, it gives you the tools to make it.
Ubernet67;-;As an Operation Flashpoint, ArmA 1, and ArmA 2 Veteran, and having played ArmA 3 for 200 hours, I can safely say that ArmA 3 is the best ArmA yet. It improves drastically on many of the previous games' flaws, as well as adding some cool new things. And I will admit, while there could be many more missions, weapons, and vehicles in the game (there's a lot less to do than in ArmA 2), it makes up for it by having steam workshop support, as well as being extensively moddable. For me, the campaign so far is the best campaign out of every ArmA game. Sure, it's no where near AAA standards, but it has more than kept my interest for far longer than ArmA 2/ArmA 1's campaigns. So all in All, I would definitely reccomend ArmA 3 to anyone who likes Tactical Shooters/Strategy and Military Simulation games.
