Samadhi;-;I can't say enough good things about ARMA 3. This is a game for someone who wants a truly lifelike military sandbox. This is not COD or BF; for the most part, run and gun tactics will only get you shot and killed here. You will have to think quickly and thoroughly to plan your assaults, escapes, etc. You will die a lot initially until you learn how to properly strategize and utilize the assets at your disposal but you will have fun doing it. The Bohemia content is a blast to play and replay but where this game really shines is in the wealth of community created content that offers something for everyone. The level editor makes it easy to create your own scenarios and tailor missions to your specific desires and play styles. Truth be told I would pay the $60.00USD for this game just to play the Breaking Point mod (think DayZ using Arma3 engine/maps) but either way, the game was well worth the money.
